The paper deals with zero-shot learning of imaging data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a generative model and an optimal transport framework, which are both techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of auxiliary attributes also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves text-based attributes, which could potentially fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the use of benchmark datasets and evaluation metrics suggests that the paper may also fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
